    • getRefId

      public static String getRefId​(com.google.gson.JsonObject obj, String refName)
      Returns the value of the `@id` field of the entity reference with the given name. For example, the given object could be an exchange and the given reference name could be `flow`, then, this method would return the reference ID of the flow.

    • asRef

      public static com.google.gson.JsonObject asRef​(Descriptor d, EntityCache cache)
      Generates a `Ref` type as defined in olca-schema. For some types (e.g. flows or processes) a more specific `Ref` type is used (e.g. `FlowRef` or `ProcessRef`) that contains additional meta-data.

    • asDescriptor

      public static com.google.gson.JsonObject asDescriptor​(Descriptor d, EntityCache cache)
      Generates a `Ref` type as defined in olca-schema. For some types (e.g. flows or processes) a more specific `Ref` type is used (e.g. `FlowRef` or `ProcessRef`) that contains additional meta-data.

    • write

      public static void write​(com.google.gson.JsonElement json, File file)
      Writes the given JSON element to the given file. Possible exceptions are rethrown as runtime exceptions.

    • readObject

      public static Optional<com.google.gson.JsonObject> readObject​(File file)
      Read the content of the given file as JSON object. If this fails an empty result is returned instead of throwing an exception.
